        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer300670194" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4681336950620974899">This is super cute and sweet as hell. I loved Christian, Marigold, Ed and the dogs...all five of them. <br/><br/>I particularly liked Ed because he reminded me of Eve Dallas (In Death series) with all his mixed cliches. Made me smile every time.<br/><br/> &quot;He&apos;d buttered his bread, and now he&apos;d have to lie in it.&quot;<br/> &quot;What&apos;s sauce for the goose, is sauce for the eager beaver.&quot;<br/> &quot;You just have to take the bear by the horns.&quot;<br/><br/>I&apos;m looking forward to Twice Upon A Marigold.</span>
  <span id="freeText4681336950620974899" style="display:none">This is super cute and sweet as hell. I loved Christian, Marigold, Ed and the dogs...all five of them. <br /><br />I particularly liked Ed because he reminded me of Eve Dallas (In Death series) with all his mixed cliches. Made me smile every time.<br /><br /> "He'd buttered his bread, and now he'd have to lie in it."<br /> "What's sauce for the goose, is sauce for the eager beaver."<br /> "You just have to take the bear by the horns."<br /><br />I'm looking forward to Twice Upon A Marigold.</span>
