        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer160639758" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15965932641119377986">Honestly, I probably would&apos;ve adored this book back in junior high. Its a cute spin on the fairytale genre, but a little too predictable. A princess in distress who is the smart outcast of her sisters, an evil queen, a fatherly king, a prince in disguise, etc etc. Also, some of the lines in the story were corny to the max and the plot seems to move extremely slow in some places.<br/>The main reason though why I&apos;m giving this one a 2 is because I didn&apos;t necessarily like some of the stereotypes that we</span>
  <span id="freeText15965932641119377986" style="display:none">Honestly, I probably would've adored this book back in junior high. Its a cute spin on the fairytale genre, but a little too predictable. A princess in distress who is the smart outcast of her sisters, an evil queen, a fatherly king, a prince in disguise, etc etc. Also, some of the lines in the story were corny to the max and the plot seems to move extremely slow in some places.<br />The main reason though why I'm giving this one a 2 is because I didn't necessarily like some of the stereotypes that were being reinforced. Yes yes, its mostly just the classic stereotypes you find in fairytales surrounding women... but still. Come on.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15965932641119377986" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

